<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14135">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Orienteering.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4159">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Show that you know first aid for the following types of injuries that
      could occur while orienteering: cuts, scratches, blisters, snakebite,
      insect stings, tick bites, heat and cold reactions (sunburn, heatstroke,
      heat exhaustion, hypothermia), dehydration. Explain to your counselor why
      you should be able to identify poisonous plants and poisonous animals that
      are found in your area. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://shopeverbeam.com/blogs/news/10-ways-to-handle-emergencies-while-orienteering-essential-tips-for-adventure-safety"
        target="_blank"
        >10 Ways to Handle Emergencies While Orienteering: Essential Tips for
        Adventure Safety (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mwAHhOwqeX4" target="_blank"
        >Tick Checks (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.weather.gov/safety/heat-illness" target="_blank"
        >Heat Cramps, Heat Exhaustion, and Heat Stroke (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/P6aBc4OAD0g" target="_blank"
        >Poisonous Plants (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4161">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain what orienteering is. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/26Zc5AVkFis?si=BBTUkJ_RFGL6VdEI" target="_blank"
        >Start Orienteering || A Newcomer's Guide (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4139">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4139 mb-requirement-id-4140">
        (a) Explain how a compass works. Describe the features of an
        orienteering compass. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bzNA6-lx5n8?si=JfVYqR9vTbCwySw5"
          target="_blank"
          >Basic Orienteering (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4139 mb-requirement-id-4141">
        (b) In the field, show how to take a compass bearing and follow it.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0cF0ovA3FtY?si=o6nQlPuwNkbBJhwu"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Compass (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4142">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/CoVcRxza8nI?si=CX1u3glYRomi-DV-" target="_blank"
        >Topographic Maps (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4143">
        (a) Explain how a topographic map shows terrain features. Point out and
        name five terrain features on a map and in the field.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4144">
        (b) Point out and name 10 symbols on a topographic map.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4145">
        (c) Explain the meaning of <em>declination</em>. Tell why you must
        consider declination when using map and compass together. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/SStmBzQC7eI?si=Le11Br8wWTxuIj0J"
          target="_blank"
          >Magnetic Declination (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4146">
        (d) Show a topographic map with magnetic north-south lines.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4147">
        (e) Show how to measure distances on a map using an orienteering
        compass.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4142 mb-requirement-id-4148">
        (f) Show how to orient a map using a compass.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4162">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Set up a 100-meter pace course. Determine your walking and running pace
      for 100 meters. Tell why it is important to pace-count. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/YAS9Cc8fhO8?si=hYookKh8Yld4_auy" target="_blank"
        >Establishing a Pace Count (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4149">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4149 mb-requirement-id-4150">
        (a) Identify 20 international control description symbols. Tell the
        meaning of each symbol. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://carolinaorienteering.com/wp-content/uploads/Orienteering-Clue-Symbols.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >International Orienteering Symbols (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4149 mb-requirement-id-4151">
        (b) Show a control description sheet and explain the information
        provided. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://orienteering-sport.com/control-descriptions"
          target="_blank"
          >Key Terms (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4149 mb-requirement-id-4152">
        (c) Explain the following terms and tell when you would use them: attack
        point, collecting feature, catching feature, aiming off, contouring,
        reading ahead, handrail, relocation, and rough versus fine orienteering.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://betterorienteering.org/intermediate-techniques"
          target="_blank"
          >Setting Up an Orienteering Course (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4153">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4153 mb-requirement-id-4154">
        (a) Take part in three orienteering events. One of these must be a
        cross-country course. <br /><br />
        <b> Note: </b>While orienteering is primarily an individual sport,
        Scouting America Youth Protection procedures call for using the buddy
        system. Requirement 7(a) can be completed by pairs or groups of Scouts.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4153 mb-requirement-id-4155">
        (b) After each event, write a report with (1) a copy of the master map
        and control description sheet, (2) a copy of the route you took on the
        course, (3) a discussion of how you could improve your time between
        control points, and (4) a list of your major weaknesses on this course .
        Describe what you could do to improve.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4156">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4156 mb-requirement-id-4157">
        (a) Set up a cross-country course that is at least 2,000 meters long
        with at least five control markers. Prepare the master map and control
        description sheet.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4156 mb-requirement-id-4158">
        (b) Set up a score orienteering course with at least 12 control points
        and a time limit of at least 60 minutes. Set point values for each
        control. Prepare the master map and control description sheet.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4163">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Act as an official during an orienteering event. This may be during the
      running of the course you set up for requirement 8. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/IfSaBKaau4k?si=e-jJhIclbeNvXswp" target="_blank"
        >How to Setup a Compass Course (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4160">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Teach orienteering techniques to your patrol, troop or crew.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
